  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hello @harshmaur, if you want to have a default selected range using the MultiRange, you could try with `defaultSelectedItem` instead of `defaultSelectedItems` (little typo here, sorry). This syntax works for a MultiRange, not a RefinementList. The RefinementList expects an array of default items. \n\nIf I look to your example you would have something like:\n\n`<VirtualMultiRange attributeName=\"price\" defaultSelectedItem=\"150000:\" />`\n\nAlso, the defaultSelectedItem you choose should match with one of the item manually declared using the `items` props. \n\nFull example with a MultiRange:\n\n``` js\n<MultiRange attributeName=\"price\"\n                items={[\n                  {end: 10, label: '<$10'},\n                  {start: 10, end: 100, label: '$10-$100'},\n                  {start: 100, end: 500, label: '$100-$500'},\n                  {start: 500, label: '>$500'},\n                ]}\n                defaultSelectedItem=\"500:\"\n/>\n```\n\nIf I wanted to select the \"<10\" by default, I would have written: `\":10\"`\n\nDefinitely our doc should be improved here. \n\nLet me know if it works better. \n",
    "created_at": "2016-10-16T11:23:40Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1408#issuecomment-254041184",
